task.summary: Final documentation fix to make it ready for publishing to github.
Github seems to use my account as root for relative links in markdown documents.
Apparently quite difficult to link to different parts of documentation. New try.
Githubs markdown apparently does not support autolinks!
Oops! Non relative links need to start with https://
And links apparently needs to be spelled correctly :-).
And making changes in the documentation of course requires me to regenerate the PDF.
Added my maven repository to the maven plugin doc.
decreased the width of horzontal rulers.
Fix code rendering bug in HTMLGenerator.
Updated pom with an url to the project home on github so that CodeLicenseManager can find and resolve this automatically.

- Comments are now only identified as comments if the start in first, second or third char. Otherwise it is a code block. - Now test for code block before list to avoid * in comments in code block to be interpreted as list items. - User guide PDF have been updated for unknown reason. Its markdown source is not updated!
- My previous fix created a new bug where list items became code blocks. This is now solved. - Cosmetica i PDF generation.
Added download link for command line executable jar to README.md.
Added download link for command line executable jar to README.md.
